%% Diagram: TAO invalidation and versioning
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant F1 as Follower 1 (originator)
    participant L as Leader
    participant F2 as Follower 2 (other tier)

    F1->>L: write x (v1 -> v2)
    L->>L: persist via MySQL write-through
    L-->>F1: changeset incl. v2
    Note over F1: F1 caches v2 (read-after-write)

    L--)F2: async invalidate {key=x, version=v2}

    alt F2 has v1 cached
        Note over F2: cached version < v2 -> drop entry
    else F2 has v2 or newer
        Note over F2: ignore (idempotent, out-of-order safe)
    else F2 has nothing
        Note over F2: no-op
    end

    Note over F1,F2: Association lists use 'refill' instead of invalidate<br/>so followers query the leader for the updated prefix.
